{"type":"message","id":"347dc84b","parentId":"a8980145","timestamp":"2026-04-15T09:58:17.530Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_frz5yg8xth9y_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"1efacff3-ca8a-47c8-9490-3a12df8f1df5\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"pet-connect-dev-stall-monitor\",\n      \"description\": \"Monitor Pet Connect developer progress and alert if development appears stalled or not progressing.\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775783758784,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775789898684,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 900000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1775783758784\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check Pet Connect developer progress in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/03-development. Focus on whether the developer appears stalled or not making progress. Inspect recent file changes in docs and src/pet-connect, especially IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_V2.md, HANDOVER.md, prisma/, src/domain/, src/application/, src/infrastructure/, and other new code. If there are signs of progress, stay silent. If developer output appears stalled, inconsistent, or not moving for too long, send a concise alert to Khuowgn with blocker/risk summary and what needs intervention. Do not ask the user questions unless intervention is truly required.\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775789158825,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 55162,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c655ef85-59da-45cc-8544-d7fcc698218e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"pet-connect-frontend-progress-followup-5m\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775787213564,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775787555248,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T02:18:00.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Re-check Pet Connect frontend progress in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/03-development/src/pet-connect. Focus on frontend-demo implementation after the frontend-first override. Inspect recent changes in src/app, src/components, src/hooks, src/lib/mock-data.ts, docs/HANDOVER.md, and any new UI/demo files. Then send Khuowgn a concise blunt progress report in Vietnamese: what frontend surfaces are done, what is still missing for a demo, whether Dev is actually following the frontend-first direction, and whether intervention is needed. Do not ask questions unless truly blocked.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 600\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775787480004,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 75244,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ef82c238-0ea1-424b-8832-fc6debc753fe\",\n      \"agentId\": \"qa-reviewer\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"driving-system-qa-full-audit-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775831302194,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775831878204,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T14:27:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Agent 04 — QA Reviewer for the driving-training system. Activate your relevant skills first, especially prompt-optimizer if applicable and your QA/review skills. This is a REPORT-ONLY audit. Do not modify frontend or backend code.\\n\\nProject roots:\\n- FE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe\\n- BE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\\n- PRD: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/PRD.md\\n- Shared context: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/PROJECT_CONTEXT_PACK.md\\n- Existing QA brief: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/04-qa-and-review/docs/TASK_BRIEF_API_UNUSED_FIELDS_AUDIT.md\\n\\nYour job: produce a QA report for the WHOLE driving-training system with separate frontend and backend findings, plus a system summary.\\n\\nRequired deliverables in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/04-qa-and-review/docs/:\\n1) DRIVING_SYSTEM_FE_QA_REPORT.md\\n2) DRIVING_SYSTEM_BE_QA_REPORT.md\\n3) DRIVING_SYSTEM_SYSTEM_QA_SUMMARY.md\\n4) API_UNUSED_FIELDS_REPORT.md\\n5) API_UNUSED_FIELDS_MATRIX.md\\n6) HANDOVER.md\\n\\nMinimum required content:\\n- Frontend report:\\n  - architecture/readability risks\\n  - route/page/component organization\\n  - state/data-fetching risks\\n  - FE↔API integration risks\\n  - UX consistency issues visible from code structure\\n  - top FE defects/risk list with severity\\n- Backend report:\\n  - controlle