\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Send this exact message to Telegram group -5163901258 (sessionKey: agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258) using sessions_send:\\n\\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | 11:53 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — **RESOLVED** ✅ — session cleared, delivery attempts ended\\n• cron:ac986a8d (Telegram delivery retry) — **RESOLVED** ✅ — no longer in sessions list, system cleaned up after ~83 min stuck period\\n• All previously-flagged stuck sessions now cleared\\n\\nPipeline: **HEALTHY** ✅\\n• Active sessions: 2 (both 5p cron monitors running stable)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Blockers: None\\n\\n— Orbis 🌐\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 30\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"-5163901258\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1776167850284,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 31562,\n        \"lastError\": \"cron: job execution timed out\",\n        \"lastErrorReason\": \"timeout\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776247097516}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb67511f","parentId":"347dc84b","timestamp":"2026-04-15T09:58:32.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the cron jobs. The issue is the heartbeat cron (`6f3323ef` and `ed2d0b5d`) which runs every 5 minutes (300000ms) and creates sessions. \n\nLooking at the issue: the report says \"Heartbeat cron creates 1 new session entry/minute → registry grows ~1MB/day\". \n\nBut looking at the jobs, the cron job creates a new session every time it runs (every 5 minutes). So over 5 minutes, one session entry is created per run. Over a day (288 5-minute intervals), that's ~288 session entries.\n\n\nEach run creates an isolated session that remains in sessions.json even after completion, so the file keeps growing. The solution is to increase the interval from 5 minutes to 15 minutes, which would cut session creation by two-thirds while still maintaining reasonable monitoring frequency. Let me verify the cron jobs are currently active and then apply the fix.\n\nLooking at the timing more carefully—the user mentioned \"1 new session entry/minute\" but the actual cron runs every 5 minutes, which suggests there might be multiple crons firing or the measurement was approximate. In any case, the fix remains the same: throttle to 15 minutes to reduce the growth rate significantly. I'll update the `everyMs` value from 300000 to 900000 milliseconds and adjust the HEARTBEAT.md documentation accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"f4de6bb1df0e06d1dead80c2079906ac57c0f5ca50ec38559be122ffd6513cc8"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the issue clearly. The two active 5p cron jobs (`6f3323ef`, `ed2d0b5d`) create a new isolated session per run. Over 5 minutes that's 288 sessions/day. Throttle to **15 minutes** (900000ms) across both crons — cuts growth by 2/3.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c23o5cef7hro_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json","offset":1,"limit":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":7501,"output":418,"cacheRead":19219,"cacheWrite":195,"totalTokens":27333,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776247097532,"responseId":"062e943a4670425745317038efedc35b"}}
