{"type":"message","id":"c0711de9","parentId":"4a0b8dc1","timestamp":"2026-04-15T10:32:07.198Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron job is reporting as \"5p Progress Report\" but I already changed the schedule to 15 minutes. The cron job still shows \"5p Progress Report\" in its name field (not just the interval). The job ran at 10:25 UTC which is within the 15-minute window (since I updated it at ~09:50). \n\nAlso, this report itself still says \"5p\" in the format. I need to update the cron job's name itself, not just the description. Let me fix the name in the jobs.json and update the format text.","thinkingSignature":"4311b93aa1872cca966ac33bcf2657797f532348d50bf2eabe600c2574f0aef5"},{"type":"text","text":"cron ran at 10:25 with old \"5p\" branding. Fix the name + format text in both cron jobs and update the report format in HEARTBEAT.md:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxorr5fmdar2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw && python3 -c \"\nimport json\n\nwith open('cron/jobs.json', 'r') as f:\n    jobs = json.load(f)\n\nrenamed = []\nfor job in jobs['jobs']:\n    if job.get('name', '').startswith('5p Progress Report') and job.get('enabled') is True:\n        old = job['name']\n        job['name'] = job['name'].replace('5p Progress Report', '15p Progress Report')\n        print(f'Renamed: {old} -> {job[\\\"name\\\"]}')\n        renamed.append(job['id'])\n\nwith open('cron/jobs.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(jobs, f, indent=2)\n    f.write('\\n')\n\nprint(f'Renamed {len(renamed)} cron jobs.')\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":357,"cacheRead":8115,"cacheWrite":21330,"totalTokens":29802,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776249117601,"responseId":"062e9c1e4657140fe2526add6d9faaa3"}}
