{"type":"message","id":"3bb68235","parentId":"fb66c732","timestamp":"2026-04-15T13:47:16.962Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear:\n- cron:6f3323ef fails with \"HTTP 502 server_error: Upstream unavailable (timeout)\" — the AI model API is temporarily down/unavailable for that region.\n- This is not a Telegram issue — it's the model endpoint failing.\n- The error says \"FallbackSummaryError: All models failed (2): ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV: HTTP 502... | ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy: HTTP 502...\"\n\nThis means both model fallbacks returned 502. This is a transient upstream API issue, not a misconfiguration. The cron is still active.\n\n\nThe job is configured to run every 15 minutes, and it should retry automatically at the next interval since the 502 was a temporary upstream failure rather than a configuration error. I should just monitor and wait for the next run to see if the service recovers. The model endpoint recovered between runs, so the cron should work on its next cycle. Since it's transient, I'll just monitor and report this to the Lead.","thinkingSignature":"409a1f72cef26037d1382583af66f04c3f2768950f5c9c9fc518a484e1aa5fe6"},{"type":"text","text":"Not a Telegram config issue — both model endpoints (`AHV-Holding-DEV` + `AHV-Holding-TroLy`) returned **502 Upstream unavailable** simultaneously. This is a transient API outage, not misconfiguration.\n\ncron:6f3323ef will auto-retry at the next 15 min interval (~13:59 UTC). If it recovers, no action needed.\n\nFlagged to Lead: the 502 error means the upstream AI model gateway was temporarily down — likely a blip. I'll monitor the next run.\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":826,"output":331,"cacheRead":33043,"cacheWrite":550,"totalTokens":34750,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776260827631,"responseId":"062ec9dc5