{"type":"message","id":"e1d03706","parentId":"85932f3f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:39:56.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead wants me to implement notification channels using:\n1. **Twilio** - for SMS\n2. **Zalo OA** - Zalo Official Account notifications\n3. **Push notification** - in-app notifications\n4. **Trigger**: any content Lead specifies\n\nI need to clarify what triggers/notifications they want. Let me think about what the system likely needs:\n\nFrom the existing codebase, I can see:\n- There's already a notification system with `notify_config` and `notify_content` collections\n- There's a `notify.service.ts` \n- There's `notify.controller.ts`\n\nThe Lead wants SMS (Twilio), Zalo OA, and in-app push notifications. Let me first explore the existing notification system to understand what's already there, then plan the implementation.\n\n\nI should map out the existing notification infrastructure—the data models, current services, and how notifications are structured—then identify what needs to be built for each channel before I start the backend work.","thinkingSignature":"d56db7c55f6987d19ff2fed8f963382194416d9197dec8cfa42600812d252cb6"},{"type":"text","text":"Rõ rồi. Để tôi survey hệ thống notification hiện tại trước khi lên kế hoạch.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_svuqafsva9z6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== BE: existing notification files ===\" && find /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src -name \"*notif*\" -o -name \"*notify*\" | sort && echo \"\" && echo \"=== BE: notification models ===\" && cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify.model.ts 2>/dev/null && echo \"\" && cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_config.model.ts 2>/dev/null && echo \"\" && cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_content.model.ts 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":163,"output":440,"cacheRead":44051,"cacheWrite":3326,"totalTokens":47980,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776285586731,"responseId":"062f2a9468819259df35976cf30a7794"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0661c00","parentId":"e1d03706","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:39:56.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_svuqafsva9z6_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== BE: existing notification files ===\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/notification.service.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/notify.service.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/domain/entities/notification.entity.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/domain/repositories/notification.repository.interface.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notification.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_config.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_content.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_user.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/notification.repository.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/notify.repository.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/notification.controller.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/notify.controller.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/dtos/notification.dto.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/routes/notification.routes.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/scripts/migrate_notifications.ts\n\n=== BE: notification models ===\n/**\n * notifies — aligned to ahv-driving-training reference.\n * Collection name: \"notifies\" (plural, all lowercase).\n * Bootstrap-backup fields moved to notifyContents.data.\n */\nimport mongoose, { Schema, Document, Model, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport const INotifyStatus = {\n  Draft: 'draft',\n  Sent: 'sent',\n  Cancel: 'cancel',\n} as const;\nexport type NotifyStatus = (typeof INotifyStatus)[keyof typeof INotifyStatus];\n\nexport interface INotify extends Document {\n  content_id: Types.ObjectId;\n  config_id: Types.ObjectId;\n  status: NotifyStatus;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst NotifySchema = new Schema<INotify>(\n  {\n    content_id: {\n      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,\n      ref: 'NotifyContent',\n      required: [true, 'content_id is required'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    config_id: {\n      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,\n      ref: 'NotifyConfigs',\n      required: [true, 'config_id is required'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    status: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: Object.values(INotifyStatus),\n      default: 'draft',\n      required: [true, 'status is required'],\n    },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    toJSON: {\n      virtuals: true,\n      transform: (_doc, ret: Record<string, unknown>) => {\n        ret.id = ret._id;\n        delete ret._id;\n        return ret;\n      },\n    },\n    toObject: {\n      virtuals: true,\n      transform: (_doc, ret: Record<string, unknown>) => {\n        ret.id = ret._id;\n        delete ret._id;\n        return ret;\n      },\n    },\n  },\n);\n\nNotifySchema.index({ created_at: -1, status: 1 });\n\nconst Notify: Model<INotify> =\n  mongoose.models.notifies ||\n  mongoose.model<INotify>('notifies', NotifySchema);\n\nexport default Notify;\n\n/**\n * NotifyConfigs — aligned to ahv-driving-training reference.\n * Exact field names preserved. Used as required config_id in notifies.\n */\nimport mongoose, { Schema, Document, Model } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport const INotifyChannelConfig = {\n  Telegram: 'Telegram',\n  Zalo: 'Zalo',\n  CMS: 'CMS',\n  Mobile: 'Mobile',\n} as const;\nexport type NotifyChannelConfig = (typeof INotifyChannelConfig)[keyof typeof INotifyChannelConfig];\n\nexport interface INotifyConfig extends Document {\n  name: string | null;\n  channel: NotifyChannelConfig;\n  channel_config: Record<string, unknown>;\n  schedule_config: { time?: string; days?: number[] } | null;\n  api_config: Record<string, unknown>;\n  active: boolean;\n  is_schedule: boolean;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst NotifyConfigSchema = new Schema<INotifyConfig>(\n  {\n    name: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    channel: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: Object.values(INotifyChannelConfig),\n      required: [true, 'channel is required'],\n    },\n    channel_config: { type: Schema.Types.Mixed, default: {} },\n    schedule_config: {\n      type: Schema.Types.Mixed,\n      default: null,\n    },\n    api_config: { type: Schema.Types.Mixed, default: {} },\n    active: { type: Boolean, default: true, index: true },\n    is_schedule: { type: Boolean, default: false, index: true },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    toJSON: { virtuals: true },\n    toObject: { virtuals: true },\n  },\n);\n\nNotifyConfigSchema.index({ active: 1, is_schedule: 1 });\n\nconst NotifyConfig: Model<INotifyConfig> =\n  mongoose.models.NotifyConfigs ||\n  mongoose.model<INotifyConfig>('NotifyConfigs', NotifyConfigSchema);\n\nexport default NotifyConfig;\n\n/**\n * notifyContents — aligned to ahv-driving-training reference.\n * Bootstrap-backup extensions stored in data{} field.\n */\nimport mongoose, { Schema, Document, Model } from 'mongoose';\n\n// Use exact ITypeNotifies from ahv-driving-training, extended with bootstrap-backup types\nexport const ITypeNotifies = {\n  // ahv-driving-training types\n  Lesson: 'lesson',\n  Coupons: 'coupons',\n  CreateLesson: 'createLesson',\n  UpdateLesson: 'updateLesson',\n  DeleteLesson: 'deleteLesson',\n  CreateExam: 'createExam',\n  UpdateExam: 'updateExam',\n  DeleteExam: 'deleteExam',\n  CreateExamSchedules: 'createExamSchedules',\n  UpdateExamRegistrationStatus: 'updateExamRegistrationStatus',\n  DeleteExamRegistrationStatus: 'deleteExamRegistrationStatus',\n  CreateStudentComment: 'createStudentComment',\n  UpdateStudentComment: 'updateStudentComment',\n  DeleteStudentComment: 'deleteStudentComment',\n  CreateTeacherComment: 'createTeacherComment',\n  UpdateTeacherComment: 'updateTeacherComment',\n  DeleteTeacherComment: 'deleteTeacherComment',\n  // bootstrap-backup extensions\n  Announcement: 'announcement',\n  System: 'system',\n  Payment: 'payment',\n  Dat: 'dat',\n  Manual: 'manual',\n} as const;\nexport type NotifyType = (typeof ITypeNotifies)[keyof typeof ITypeNotifies];\n\nexport interface INotifyContent extends Document {\n  title: string | null;\n  sub_title: string | null;\n  content: string | null;\n  sub_content: string | null;\n  types: NotifyType;\n  data: {\n    // bootstrap-backup extensions (moved from notifies model)\n    source_type?: string;\n    source_id?: string;\n    channel?: string;\n    target_group?: string;\n    scheduled_at?: Date;\n    created_by?: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;\n    channels?: string[];\n    // legacy data from Notification/Announcement\n    [key: string]: unknown;\n  } | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst NotifyContentSchema = new Schema<INotifyContent>(\n  {\n    title: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    sub_title: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    content: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    sub_content: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    types: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: Object.values(ITypeNotifies),\n      required: [true, 'types is required'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    data: { type: Schema.Types.Mixed, default: null },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    toJSON: { virtuals: true },\n    toObject: { virtuals: true },\n  },\n);\n\nNotifyContentSchema.index({ types: 1, created_at: -1 });\n\nconst NotifyContent: Model<INotifyContent> =\n  mongoose.models.NotifyContent ||\n  mongoose.model<INotifyContent>('NotifyContent', NotifyContentSchema);\n\nexport default NotifyContent;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":112,"aggregated":"=== BE: existing notification files ===\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/notification.service.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/notify.service.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/domain/entities/notification.entity.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/domain/repositories/notification.repository.interface.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notification.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_config.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_content.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notify_user.model.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/notification.repository.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/notify.repository.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/notification.controller.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/notify.controller.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/dtos/notification.dto.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/routes/notification.routes.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/scripts/migrate_notifications.ts\n\n=== BE: notification models ===\n/**\n * notifies — aligned to ahv-driving-training reference.\n * Collection name: \"notifies\" (plural, all lowercase).\n * Bootstrap-backup fields moved to notifyContents.data.\n */\nimport mongoose, { Schema, Document, Model, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport const INotifyStatus = {\n  Draft: 'draft',\n  Sent: 'sent',\n  Cancel: 'cancel',\n} as const;\nexport type NotifyStatus = (typeof INotifyStatus)[keyof typeof INotifyStatus];\n\nexport interface INotify extends Document {\n  content_id: Types.ObjectId;\n  config_id: Types.ObjectId;\n  status: NotifyStatus;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst NotifySchema = new Schema<INotify>(\n  {\n    content_id: {\n      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,\n      ref: 'NotifyContent',\n      required: [true, 'content_id is required'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    config_id: {\n      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,\n      ref: 'NotifyConfigs',\n      required: [true, 'config_id is required'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    status: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: Object.values(INotifyStatus),\n      default: 'draft',\n      required: [true, 'status is required'],\n    },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    toJSON: {\n      virtuals: true,\n      transform: (_doc, ret: Record<string, unknown>) => {\n        ret.id = ret._id;\n        delete ret._id;\n        return ret;\n      },\n    },\n    toObject: {\n      virtuals: true,\n      transform: (_doc, ret: Record<string, unknown>) => {\n        ret.id = ret._id;\n        delete ret._id;\n        return ret;\n      },\n    },\n  },\n);\n\nNotifySchema.index({ created_at: -1, status: 1 });\n\nconst Notify: Model<INotify> =\n  mongoose.models.notifies ||\n  mongoose.model<INotify>('notifies', NotifySchema);\n\nexport default Notify;\n\n/**\n * NotifyConfigs — aligned to ahv-driving-training reference.\n * Exact field names preserved. Used as required config_id in notifies.\n */\nimport mongoose, { Schema, Document, Model } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport const INotifyChannelConfig = {\n  Telegram: 'Telegram',\n  Zalo: 'Zalo',\n  CMS: 'CMS',\n  Mobile: 'Mobile',\n} as const;\nexport type NotifyChannelConfig = (typeof INotifyChannelConfig)[keyof typeof INotifyChannelConfig];\n\nexport interface INotifyConfig extends Document {\n  name: string | null;\n  channel: NotifyChannelConfig;\n  channel_config: Record<string, unknown>;\n  schedule_config: { time?: string; days?: number[] } | null;\n  api_config: Record<string, unknown>;\n  active: boolean;\n  is_schedule: boolean;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst NotifyConfigSchema = new Schema<INotifyConfig>(\n  {\n    name: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    channel: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: Object.values(INotifyChannelConfig),\n      required: [true, 'channel is required'],\n    },\n    channel_config: { type: Schema.Types.Mixed, default: {} },\n    schedule_config: {\n      type: Schema.Types.Mixed,\n      default: null,\n    },\n    api_config: { type: Schema.Types.Mixed, default: {} },\n    active: { type: Boolean, default: true, index: true },\n    is_schedule: { type: Boolean, default: false, index: true },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    toJSON: { virtuals: true },\n    toObject: { virtuals: true },\n  },\n);\n\nNotifyConfigSchema.index({ active: 1, is_schedule: 1 });\n\nconst NotifyConfig: Model<INotifyConfig> =\n  mongoose.models.NotifyConfigs ||\n  mongoose.model<INotifyConfig>('NotifyConfigs', NotifyConfigSchema);\n\nexport default NotifyConfig;\n\n/**\n * notifyContents — aligned to ahv-driving-training reference.\n * Bootstrap-backup extensions stored in data{} field.\n */\nimport mongoose, { Schema, Document, Model } from 'mongoose';\n\n// Use exact ITypeNotifies from ahv-driving-training, extended with bootstrap-backup types\nexport const ITypeNotifies = {\n  // ahv-driving-training types\n  Lesson: 'lesson',\n  Coupons: 'coupons',\n  CreateLesson: 'createLesson',\n  UpdateLesson: 'updateLesson',\n  DeleteLesson: 'deleteLesson',\n  CreateExam: 'createExam',\n  UpdateExam: 'updateExam',\n  DeleteExam: 'deleteExam',\n  CreateExamSchedules: 'createExamSchedules',\n  UpdateExamRegistrationStatus: 'updateExamRegistrationStatus',\n  DeleteExamRegistrationStatus: 'deleteExamRegistrationStatus',\n  CreateStudentComment: 'createStudentComment',\n  UpdateStudentComment: 'updateStudentComment',\n  DeleteStudentComment: 'deleteStudentComment',\n  CreateTeacherComment: 'createTeacherComment',\n  UpdateTeacherComment: 'updateTeacherComment',\n  DeleteTeacherComment: 'deleteTeacherComment',\n  // bootstrap-backup extensions\n  Announcement: 'announcement',\n  System: 'system',\n  Payment: 'payment',\n  Dat: 'dat',\n  Manual: 'manual',\n} as const;\nexport type NotifyType = (typeof ITypeNotifies)[keyof typeof ITypeNotifies];\n\nexport interface INotifyContent extends Document {\n  title: string | null;\n  sub_title: string | null;\n  content: string | null;\n  sub_content: string | null;\n  types: NotifyType;\n  data: {\n    // bootstrap-backup extensions (moved from notifies model)\n    source_type?: string;\n    source_id?: string;\n    channel?: string;\n    target_group?: string;\n    scheduled_at?: Date;\n    created_by?: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;\n    channels?: string[];\n    // legacy data from Notification/Announcement\n    [key: string]: unknown;\n  } | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst NotifyContentSchema = new Schema<INotifyContent>(\n  {\n    title: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    sub_title: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    content: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    sub_content: { type: String, default: null, trim: true },\n    types: {\n      type: String,\n      enum: Object.values(ITypeNotifies),\n      required: [true, 'types is required'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    data: { type: Schema.Types.Mixed, default: null },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    toJSON: { virtuals: true },\n    toObject: { virtuals: true },\n  },\n);\n\nNotifyContentSchema.index({ types: 1, created_at: -1 });\n\nconst NotifyContent: Model<INotifyContent> =\n  mongoose.models.NotifyContent ||\n  mongoose.model<INotifyContent>('NotifyContent', NotifyContentSchema);\n\nexport default NotifyContent;","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776285596455}}
{"type":"message","id":"95a20fb1","parentId":"c0661c00","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:40:09.217Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now I have a clear picture of the existing notification system:\n\n1. **notifyContent** - stores the actual notification content (title, sub_title, content, sub_content, types)\n2. **notifyConfig** - channel config (Telegram, Zalo, CMS, Mobile) with channel_config and api_config\n3. **notify** - junction table linking content to config with status (draft, sent, cancel)\n\nThe current channels are: Telegram, Zalo, CMS, Mobile\n\nNow I need to add:\n- **SMS via Twilio** - need to integrate Twilio SDK\n- **Zalo OA Push** - Zalo API for Official Account\n\n\n- **In-app Push Notification** - need FCM or similar\n\nThe system already supports channel configs with api_config fields, so I need to extend the NotifyChannelConfig enum to include SMS, then add the integration services for Twilio SMS and Zalo OA notifications, while leveraging the existing in-app notification storage and expanding the frontend to display real-time push notifications through Firebase Cloud Messaging or WebSocket.","thinkingSignature":"b977e90d093b6b3ede47e630b33bd2683baf68d4e35bb07f1a788c8dbae55fc9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6l34s5v8x4z7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== notify.service.ts ===\" && cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/notify.service.ts && echo \"\" && echo \"=== notify.controller.ts ===\" && cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/notify.controller.ts && echo \"\" && echo \"=== notify.routes ===\" && grep -n \"notif\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/routes/index.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2229,"output":372,"cacheRead":47194,"cacheWrite":661,"totalTokens":50456,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776285596494,"responseId":"062f2a9d7049683edca1d450253736b2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"51ff7969","parentId":"95a20fb1","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:40:09.422Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6l34s5v8x4z7_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== notify.service.ts ===\n/**\n * NotifyService — adapter layer for 4-collection model.\n * Maps to existing API response shapes expected by FE.\n * Replaces NotificationService + AnnouncementService.\n */\nimport { NotifyRepository, AdaptedNotification } from '@/infrastructure/database/repositories/notify.repository';\nimport { PaginationOptions, PaginatedResult } from '@/domain/types/pagination.types';\nimport NotifyContent from '@/infrastructure/database/models/notify_content.model';\nimport Notify from '@/infrastructure/database/models/notify.model';\nimport { Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport class NotifyService {\n  private repo: NotifyRepository;\n\n  constructor() {\n    this.repo = new NotifyRepository();\n  }\n\n  // ── Notifications (per-user) ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async getByUser(\n    userId: string,\n    options?: PaginationOptions,\n  ): Promise<PaginatedResult<AdaptedNotification>> {\n    return this.repo.findByUserId(userId, options);\n  }\n\n  async send(data: {\n    userId: string;\n    title: string;\n    content: string;\n    channel?: string;\n    data?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  }): Promise<AdaptedNotification> {\n    return this.repo.sendNotification(data);\n  }\n\n  async markAsRead(notifyUserId: string, userId: string) {\n    return this.repo.markAsRead(notifyUserId, userId);\n  }\n\n  async markAllAsRead(userId: string) {\n    return this.repo.markAllAsRead(userId);\n  }\n\n  async getUnreadCount(userId: string): Promise<number> {\n    return this.repo.countUnreadByUserId(userId);\n  }\n\n  async deleteNotification(notifyUserId: string, userId?: string) {\n    // Find the NotifyUser to get the notify_id, then delete from notifyUsers\n    return this.repo.deleteNotifyUser(notifyUserId, userId);\n  }\n\n  // ── Announcements (admin broadcast) ────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async getAnnouncements(options: PaginationOptions & { search?: string; status?: string }) {\n    const { page, limit, search, status } = options;\n    const skip = (page - 1) * limit;\n\n    const query: Record<string, unknown> = { types: 'announcement' };\n    if (search) {\n      query.$or = [\n        { title: { $regex: search, $options: 'i' } },\n        { content: { $regex: search, $options: 'i' } },\n      ];\n    }\n    if (status) {\n      // Map FE status to notifies.status\n      const notifyStatusMap: Record<string, string> = {\n        SENT: 'sent',\n        SCHEDULED: 'draft',\n      };\n      // For now, filter by content status via data lookup\n      // (simplified: just return all announcements sorted by created_at desc)\n    }\n\n    const [docs, total] = await Promise.all([\n      NotifyContent.find(query).sort({ created_at: -1 }).skip(skip).limit(limit).lean().exec(),\n      NotifyContent.countDocuments(query).exec(),\n    ]);\n\n    const data = await Promise.all(\n      docs.map(async (doc) => {\n        const notify = await Notify.findOne({ content_id: doc._id }).lean().exec();\n        const extra = (doc.data || {}) as Record<string, unknown>;\n        return {\n          id: doc._id.toString(),\n          title: doc.title,\n          content: doc.content,\n          sub_title: doc.sub_title,\n          sub_content: doc.sub_content,\n          target_group: (extra.target_group as string) || 'ALL',\n          channels: (extra.channels as string[]) || [],\n          status: notify?.status === 'sent' ? 'SENT' : 'SCHEDULED',\n          scheduled_at: extra.scheduled_at,\n          created_by: extra.created_by,\n          createdAt: doc.created_at,\n          updatedAt: doc.updated_at,\n        };\n      }),\n    );\n\n    return {\n      data,\n      meta: {\n        total,\n        page,\n        limit,\n        total_pages: Math.ceil(total / limit),\n      },\n    };\n  }\n\n  async createAnnouncement(data: {\n    title: string;\n    content: string;\n    target_group: string;\n    channels: string[];\n    status?: string;\n    scheduled_at?: Date;\n    created_by?: string;\n  }) {\n    const result = await this.repo.broadcastAnnouncement({\n      title: data.title,\n      content: data.content,\n      types: 'announcement',\n      target_group: data.target_group,\n      channels: data.channels,\n      scheduled_at: data.scheduled_at,\n      created_by: data.created_by ? new Types.ObjectId(data.created_by) : undefined,\n      status: data.status === 'SENT' ? 'sent' : 'draft',\n    });\n\n    return {\n      id: ((result.notify as unknown) as { _id: Types.ObjectId })._id.toString(),\n      title: data.title,\n      content: data.content,\n      target_group: data.target_group,\n      channels: data.channels,\n      status: data.status || 'SENT',\n      scheduled_at: data.scheduled_at,\n      created_by: data.created_by,\n      createdAt: ((result.notify as unknown) as { created_at: Date }).created_at,\n      updatedAt: ((result.notify as unknown) as { updated_at: Date }).updated_at,\n    };\n  }\n\n  async updateAnnouncement(id: string, data: Partial<{\n    title: string;\n    content: string;\n    target_group: string;\n    channels: string[];\n    status: string;\n    scheduled_at: Date;\n  }>) {\n    const content = await NotifyContent.findByIdAndUpdate(\n      id,\n      {\n        $set: {\n          ...(data.title ? { title: data.title } : {}),\n          ...(data.content ? { content: data.content } : {}),\n          'data.target_group': data.target_group,\n          'data.channels': data.channels,\n        },\n      },\n      { new: true },\n    ).lean().exec();\n\n    if (!content) return null;\n\n    const notify = await Notify.findOneAndUpdate(\n      { content_id: new Types.ObjectId(id) },\n      {\n        $set: {\n          status: data.status === 'SENT' ? 'sent' : 'draft',\n        },\n      },\n      { new: true },\n    ).lean().exec();\n\n    return content ? {\n      id: content._id.toString(),\n      ...content,\n      status: notify?.status,\n    } : null;\n  }\n\n  async deleteAnnouncement(id: string) {\n    const notify = await Notify.findOneAndDelete({ content_id: new Types.ObjectId(id) }).lean().exec();\n    if (notify) {\n      await this.repo.deleteNotifyUser(notify._id.toString());\n    }\n    const result = await NotifyContent.findByIdAndDelete(id).lean().exec();\n    return !!result;\n  }\n}\n\n=== notify.controller.ts ===\n/**\n * NotifyController — HTTP handlers for notification + announcement endpoints.\n * Uses NotifyService (4-collection model), preserves existing route paths.\n */\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { NotifyService } from '@/application/services/notify.service';\nimport { ctrlLogger } from '@/infrastructure/logging/controller-logger';\n\n// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/** Normalize Express param which can be string | string[] → string */\nconst param = (val: string | string[] | undefined): string =>\n  Array.isArray(val) ? val[0] ?? '' : (val ?? '');\n\n/** Normalize Express query which can be string | string[] → string */\nconst query = (val: string | string[] | undefined): string =>\n  Array.isArray(val) ? val[0] ?? '' : (val ?? '');\n\n// ─── Service instance ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst notifyService = new NotifyService();\n\n// ─── Notification handlers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const getNotificationsByUser = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.get_by_user', req);\n  const userId = param(req.params.userId);\n  log.start({ userId });\n\n  const result = await notifyService.getByUser(userId, req.pagination);\n  log.success(res, result, 'Notifications retrieved');\n};\n\nexport const sendNotification = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.send', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const { receive_id, title, body, channel, data } = req.body;\n  const userId = receive_id as string;\n\n  if (!userId) {\n    res.status(400).json({ success: false, message: 'receive_id is required' });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const result = await notifyService.send({\n    userId,\n    title: title || 'Thông báo',\n    content: body || '',\n    channel: channel || 'in_app',\n    data: data || {},\n  });\n  log.success(res, result, 'Notification sent');\n};\n\nexport const markAsRead = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.mark_read', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  const userId = param((req as Request & { user?: { id: string } }).user?.id ?? req.query.userId as string | undefined);\n  log.start({ notifyId: id, userId });\n\n  await notifyService.markAsRead(id, userId);\n  log.success(res, null, 'Marked as read');\n};\n\nexport const markAllAsRead = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.mark_all_read', req);\n  const userId = param(req.params.userId);\n  log.start({ userId });\n\n  await notifyService.markAllAsRead(userId);\n  log.success(res, null, 'All marked as read');\n};\n\nexport const deleteNotification = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.delete', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  const userId = param((req as Request & { user?: { id: string } }).user?.id ?? req.query.userId as string | undefined);\n  log.start({ notifyId: id, userId });\n\n  await notifyService.deleteNotification(id, userId);\n  log.success(res, null, 'Notification deleted');\n};\n\n// ─── Announcement handlers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const getAnnouncements = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.get_announcements', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const search = query(req.query.search as string | string[] | undefined);\n  const status = query(req.query.status as string | string[] | undefined);\n\n  const result = await notifyService.getAnnouncements({\n    page: req.pagination?.page ?? 1,\n    limit: req.pagination?.limit ?? 10,\n    search: search || undefined,\n    status: status || undefined,\n  });\n  log.success(res, result, 'Announcements retrieved');\n};\n\nexport const createAnnouncement = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.create_announcement', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const { title, content, target_group, channels, status, scheduled_at } = req.body;\n  const created_by = (req as Request & { user?: { id: string } }).user?.id;\n\n  const result = await notifyService.createAnnouncement({\n    title,\n    content,\n    target_group: target_group || 'ALL',\n    channels: channels || [],\n    status: status || 'SENT',\n    scheduled_at: scheduled_at ? new Date(scheduled_at) : undefined,\n    created_by,\n  });\n  log.success(res, result, 'Announcement created');\n};\n\nexport const updateAnnouncement = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.update_announcement', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  log.start({ id });\n\n  const result = await notifyService.updateAnnouncement(id, req.body);\n  if (!result) {\n    res.status(404).json({ success: false, message: 'Announcement not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  log.success(res, result, 'Announcement updated');\n};\n\nexport const deleteAnnouncement = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.delete_announcement', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  log.start({ id });\n\n  const deleted = await notifyService.deleteAnnouncement(id);\n  if (!deleted) {\n    res.status(404).json({ success: false, message: 'Announcement not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  log.success(res, null, 'Announcement deleted');\n};\n\n=== notify.routes ===\n9:import notificationRoutes from \"./notification.routes\";\n48:router.use(\"/notifications\", notificationRoutes);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":143,"aggregated":"=== notify.service.ts ===\n/**\n * NotifyService — adapter layer for 4-collection model.\n * Maps to existing API response shapes expected by FE.\n * Replaces NotificationService + AnnouncementService.\n */\nimport { NotifyRepository, AdaptedNotification } from '@/infrastructure/database/repositories/notify.repository';\nimport { PaginationOptions, PaginatedResult } from '@/domain/types/pagination.types';\nimport NotifyContent from '@/infrastructure/database/models/notify_content.model';\nimport Notify from '@/infrastructure/database/models/notify.model';\nimport { Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport class NotifyService {\n  private repo: NotifyRepository;\n\n  constructor() {\n    this.repo = new NotifyRepository();\n  }\n\n  // ── Notifications (per-user) ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async getByUser(\n    userId: string,\n    options?: PaginationOptions,\n  ): Promise<PaginatedResult<AdaptedNotification>> {\n    return this.repo.findByUserId(userId, options);\n  }\n\n  async send(data: {\n    userId: string;\n    title: string;\n    content: string;\n    channel?: string;\n    data?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  }): Promise<AdaptedNotification> {\n    return this.repo.sendNotification(data);\n  }\n\n  async markAsRead(notifyUserId: string, userId: string) {\n    return this.repo.markAsRead(notifyUserId, userId);\n  }\n\n  async markAllAsRead(userId: string) {\n    return this.repo.markAllAsRead(userId);\n  }\n\n  async getUnreadCount(userId: string): Promise<number> {\n    return this.repo.countUnreadByUserId(userId);\n  }\n\n  async deleteNotification(notifyUserId: string, userId?: string) {\n    // Find the NotifyUser to get the notify_id, then delete from notifyUsers\n    return this.repo.deleteNotifyUser(notifyUserId, userId);\n  }\n\n  // ── Announcements (admin broadcast) ────────────────────────────────────────\n\n  async getAnnouncements(options: PaginationOptions & { search?: string; status?: string }) {\n    const { page, limit, search, status } = options;\n    const skip = (page - 1) * limit;\n\n    const query: Record<string, unknown> = { types: 'announcement' };\n    if (search) {\n      query.$or = [\n        { title: { $regex: search, $options: 'i' } },\n        { content: { $regex: search, $options: 'i' } },\n      ];\n    }\n    if (status) {\n      // Map FE status to notifies.status\n      const notifyStatusMap: Record<string, string> = {\n        SENT: 'sent',\n        SCHEDULED: 'draft',\n      };\n      // For now, filter by content status via data lookup\n      // (simplified: just return all announcements sorted by created_at desc)\n    }\n\n    const [docs, total] = await Promise.all([\n      NotifyContent.find(query).sort({ created_at: -1 }).skip(skip).limit(limit).lean().exec(),\n      NotifyContent.countDocuments(query).exec(),\n    ]);\n\n    const data = await Promise.all(\n      docs.map(async (doc) => {\n        const notify = await Notify.findOne({ content_id: doc._id }).lean().exec();\n        const extra = (doc.data || {}) as Record<string, unknown>;\n        return {\n          id: doc._id.toString(),\n          title: doc.title,\n          content: doc.content,\n          sub_title: doc.sub_title,\n          sub_content: doc.sub_content,\n          target_group: (extra.target_group as string) || 'ALL',\n          channels: (extra.channels as string[]) || [],\n          status: notify?.status === 'sent' ? 'SENT' : 'SCHEDULED',\n          scheduled_at: extra.scheduled_at,\n          created_by: extra.created_by,\n          createdAt: doc.created_at,\n          updatedAt: doc.updated_at,\n        };\n      }),\n    );\n\n    return {\n      data,\n      meta: {\n        total,\n        page,\n        limit,\n        total_pages: Math.ceil(total / limit),\n      },\n    };\n  }\n\n  async createAnnouncement(data: {\n    title: string;\n    content: string;\n    target_group: string;\n    channels: string[];\n    status?: string;\n    scheduled_at?: Date;\n    created_by?: string;\n  }) {\n    const result = await this.repo.broadcastAnnouncement({\n      title: data.title,\n      content: data.content,\n      types: 'announcement',\n      target_group: data.target_group,\n      channels: data.channels,\n      scheduled_at: data.scheduled_at,\n      created_by: data.created_by ? new Types.ObjectId(data.created_by) : undefined,\n      status: data.status === 'SENT' ? 'sent' : 'draft',\n    });\n\n    return {\n      id: ((result.notify as unknown) as { _id: Types.ObjectId })._id.toString(),\n      title: data.title,\n      content: data.content,\n      target_group: data.target_group,\n      channels: data.channels,\n      status: data.status || 'SENT',\n      scheduled_at: data.scheduled_at,\n      created_by: data.created_by,\n      createdAt: ((result.notify as unknown) as { created_at: Date }).created_at,\n      updatedAt: ((result.notify as unknown) as { updated_at: Date }).updated_at,\n    };\n  }\n\n  async updateAnnouncement(id: string, data: Partial<{\n    title: string;\n    content: string;\n    target_group: string;\n    channels: string[];\n    status: string;\n    scheduled_at: Date;\n  }>) {\n    const content = await NotifyContent.findByIdAndUpdate(\n      id,\n      {\n        $set: {\n          ...(data.title ? { title: data.title } : {}),\n          ...(data.content ? { content: data.content } : {}),\n          'data.target_group': data.target_group,\n          'data.channels': data.channels,\n        },\n      },\n      { new: true },\n    ).lean().exec();\n\n    if (!content) return null;\n\n    const notify = await Notify.findOneAndUpdate(\n      { content_id: new Types.ObjectId(id) },\n      {\n        $set: {\n          status: data.status === 'SENT' ? 'sent' : 'draft',\n        },\n      },\n      { new: true },\n    ).lean().exec();\n\n    return content ? {\n      id: content._id.toString(),\n      ...content,\n      status: notify?.status,\n    } : null;\n  }\n\n  async deleteAnnouncement(id: string) {\n    const notify = await Notify.findOneAndDelete({ content_id: new Types.ObjectId(id) }).lean().exec();\n    if (notify) {\n      await this.repo.deleteNotifyUser(notify._id.toString());\n    }\n    const result = await NotifyContent.findByIdAndDelete(id).lean().exec();\n    return !!result;\n  }\n}\n\n=== notify.controller.ts ===\n/**\n * NotifyController — HTTP handlers for notification + announcement endpoints.\n * Uses NotifyService (4-collection model), preserves existing route paths.\n */\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { NotifyService } from '@/application/services/notify.service';\nimport { ctrlLogger } from '@/infrastructure/logging/controller-logger';\n\n// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/** Normalize Express param which can be string | string[] → string */\nconst param = (val: string | string[] | undefined): string =>\n  Array.isArray(val) ? val[0] ?? '' : (val ?? '');\n\n/** Normalize Express query which can be string | string[] → string */\nconst query = (val: string | string[] | undefined): string =>\n  Array.isArray(val) ? val[0] ?? '' : (val ?? '');\n\n// ─── Service instance ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst notifyService = new NotifyService();\n\n// ─── Notification handlers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const getNotificationsByUser = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.get_by_user', req);\n  const userId = param(req.params.userId);\n  log.start({ userId });\n\n  const result = await notifyService.getByUser(userId, req.pagination);\n  log.success(res, result, 'Notifications retrieved');\n};\n\nexport const sendNotification = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.send', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const { receive_id, title, body, channel, data } = req.body;\n  const userId = receive_id as string;\n\n  if (!userId) {\n    res.status(400).json({ success: false, message: 'receive_id is required' });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const result = await notifyService.send({\n    userId,\n    title: title || 'Thông báo',\n    content: body || '',\n    channel: channel || 'in_app',\n    data: data || {},\n  });\n  log.success(res, result, 'Notification sent');\n};\n\nexport const markAsRead = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.mark_read', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  const userId = param((req as Request & { user?: { id: string } }).user?.id ?? req.query.userId as string | undefined);\n  log.start({ notifyId: id, userId });\n\n  await notifyService.markAsRead(id, userId);\n  log.success(res, null, 'Marked as read');\n};\n\nexport const markAllAsRead = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.mark_all_read', req);\n  const userId = param(req.params.userId);\n  log.start({ userId });\n\n  await notifyService.markAllAsRead(userId);\n  log.success(res, null, 'All marked as read');\n};\n\nexport const deleteNotification = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.delete', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  const userId = param((req as Request & { user?: { id: string } }).user?.id ?? req.query.userId as string | undefined);\n  log.start({ notifyId: id, userId });\n\n  await notifyService.deleteNotification(id, userId);\n  log.success(res, null, 'Notification deleted');\n};\n\n// ─── Announcement handlers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const getAnnouncements = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.get_announcements', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const search = query(req.query.search as string | string[] | undefined);\n  const status = query(req.query.status as string | string[] | undefined);\n\n  const result = await notifyService.getAnnouncements({\n    page: req.pagination?.page ?? 1,\n    limit: req.pagination?.limit ?? 10,\n    search: search || undefined,\n    status: status || undefined,\n  });\n  log.success(res, result, 'Announcements retrieved');\n};\n\nexport const createAnnouncement = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.create_announcement', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const { title, content, target_group, channels, status, scheduled_at } = req.body;\n  const created_by = (req as Request & { user?: { id: string } }).user?.id;\n\n  const result = await notifyService.createAnnouncement({\n    title,\n    content,\n    target_group: target_group || 'ALL',\n    channels: channels || [],\n    status: status || 'SENT',\n    scheduled_at: scheduled_at ? new Date(scheduled_at) : undefined,\n    created_by,\n  });\n  log.success(res, result, 'Announcement created');\n};\n\nexport const updateAnnouncement = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.update_announcement', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  log.start({ id });\n\n  const result = await notifyService.updateAnnouncement(id, req.body);\n  if (!result) {\n    res.status(404).json({ success: false, message: 'Announcement not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  log.success(res, result, 'Announcement updated');\n};\n\nexport const deleteAnnouncement = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('notify.delete_announcement', req);\n  const id = param(req.params.id);\n  log.start({ id });\n\n  const deleted = await notifyService.deleteAnnouncement(id);\n  if (!deleted) {\n    res.status(404).json({ success: false, message: 'Announcement not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  log.success(res, null, 'Announcement deleted');\n};\n\n=== notify.routes ===\n9:import notificationRoutes from \"./notification.routes\";\n48:router.use(\"/notifications\", notificationRoutes);","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776285609395}}
