{"type":"message","id":"67cb96ac","parentId":"c78e489c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:43:41.021Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_98oov7ve99c4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Paths: 23\n  /auth/login\n  /auth/register\n  /auth/me\n  /auth/change-password\n  /auth/logout\n  /students\n  /students/export\n  /students/{id}\n  /courses\n  /exams\n  /exam-batches\n  /exam-schedules\n  /lessons\n  /payments\n  /payments/stats\n  /dashboard/stats\n  /dat/analytics\n  /announcements\n  /cities\n  /stadiums\n  /vip-qr\n  /settings\n  /notifications/user/{userId}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":67,"aggregated":"Paths: 23\n  /auth/login\n  /auth/register\n  /auth/me\n  /auth/change-password\n  /auth/logout\n  /students\n  /students/export\n  /students/{id}\n  /courses\n  /exams\n  /exam-batches\n  /exam-schedules\n  /lessons\n  /payments\n  /payments/stats\n  /dashboard/stats\n  /dat/analytics\n  /announcements\n  /cities\n  /stadiums\n  /vip-qr\n  /settings\n  /notifications/user/{userId}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776285820992}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee2171ac","parentId":"67cb96ac","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:44:12.321Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - Swagger is already set up but only has 23 paths. Many routes are missing. Let me now start the implementation. I'll spawn a subagent to handle the notification channels and then handle the swagger + cleanup myself.\n\nActually, given the scope of work, let me spawn two subagents:\n1. senior-backend: implement notification channels (Twilio, Zalo, FCM) + update NotifyService\n2. Then myself: swagger docs + code cleanup\n\nBut first, let me check if there's a confluence PRD that describes the remaining features.\n\nLet me also check what's missing from the swagger vs actual routes:\n\n\n- Auth, Students, Courses, Exams, Exam batches, Exam schedules, Lessons all have partial coverage\n- Payments, Dashboard, Cities, Stadiums, and announcements need checking\n- Licenses, VIP QR codes, Settings, and Notifications all need their routes documented\n\nI'm going to spawn the backend subagent first to handle the notification channels, then I'll tackle the swagger documentation myself.\n\nActually, I should focus on what I can control directly. I'll start with the channel services for Twilio SMS, Zalo OA, and FCM push notifications, update the notify service to use these channels, and handle the .env.example configuration and swagger documentation myself.","thinkingSignature":"6f94c07fcf1e2270131ed12ce05e2dc131f87043b3add8997b7f4c5d92cc2877"},{"type":"text","text":"Swagger đã có sẵn (23 paths) nhưng thiếu nhiều routes. Scope rõ — bắt đầu implementation.\n\nSpawn senior-backend để implement notification channels (Twilio/Zalo/FCM), tôi handle Swagger + cleanup:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ekakv96eqpp_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-backend working on branch `feat/notification-channel` in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be`.\n\n## Task: Implement notification channel providers (SMS via Twilio, Zalo OA, Push via FCM)\n\n### Context\nThe system already has:\n- `NotifyService` in `src/application/services/notify.service.ts` — sends to DB\n- `NotifyRepository` in `src/infrastructure/database/repositories/notify.repository.ts`\n- `notify_content` + `notify` + `notify_configs` + `notify_user` MongoDB collections\n- Channel config enum in `notify.model.ts`: `Telegram | Zalo | CMS | Mobile`\n- `.env` file with `PORT=5555`, `MONGODB_URI`, etc.\n\n### What to build\n\n**1. Channel provider services** (create new files):\n\n`src/infrastructure/channels/twilio-sms.service.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport twilio from 'twilio';\n\nconst client = twilio(\n  process.env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID,\n  process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\n);\n\nexport class TwilioSmsService {\n  async send(phone: string, message: string): Promise<{ sid: string; status: string }> {\n    return client.messages.create({\n      body: message,\n      from: process.env.TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER,\n      to: phone,\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`src/infrastructure/channels/zalo-oa.service.ts`:\n```typescript\n// Zalo OA API v3 — send text message\nexport class ZaloOaService {\n  private appId = process.env.ZALO_APP_ID!;\n  private appSecret = process.env.ZALO_APP_SECRET!;\n  private oaId = process.env.ZALO_OA_ID!;\n  private accessToken: string | null = null;\n  private tokenExpiry = 0;\n\n  private async getAccessToken(): Promise<string> {\n    if (this.accessToken && Date.now() < this.tokenExpiry) {\n      return this.accessToken;\n    }\n    const res = await fetch(\n      `https://graph.zalo.me/v2.0/oa/access_token?app_id=${this.appId}&app_secret=${this.appSecret}&grant_type=client_credentials`,\n      { method: 'POST' }\n    );\n    const data = await res.json();\n    this.accessToken = data.access_token;\n    this.tokenExpiry = Date.now() + (data.expires_in - 60) * 1000;\n    return this.accessToken;\n  }\n\n  async sendText(userId: string, message: string): Promise<{ success: boolean }> {\n    const token = await this.getAccessToken();\n    const res = await fetch(`https://graph.zalo.me/v2.0/zsns/user_message`, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n        Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,\n        access_token: this.accessToken,\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        recipient: { user_id: userId },\n        message: { text },\n        oa_id: this.oaId,\n      }),\n    });\n    return res.json();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`src/infrastructure/channels/fcm-push.service.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport { initializeApp, getApps } from 'firebase-admin/app';\nimport { getMessaging } from 'firebase-admin/messaging';\n\n// Lazy init\nlet messaging: ReturnType<typeof getMessaging> | null = null;\nconst getMessagingClient = () => {\n  if (!messaging) {\n    if (!getApps().length) {\n      initializeApp({ credential: JSON.parse(process.env.FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT || '{}') });\n    }\n    messaging = getMessaging();\n  }\n  return messaging;\n};\n\nexport class FcmPushService {\n  async sendToToken(token: string, notification: { title: string; body: string }, data?: Record<string, string>): Promise<string> {\n    const msgId = await getMessagingClient().send({\n      token,\n      notification,\n      data,\n      android: { priority: 'high' },\n      apns: { payload: { aps: { contentAvailable: true } } },\n    });\n    return msgId;\n  }\n\n  async sendToTopic(topic: string, notification: { title: string; body: string }, data?: Record<string, string>): Promise<string> {\n    const msgId = await getMessagingClient().send({\n      topic,\n      notification,\n      data,\n    });\n    return msgId;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**2. Unified notification dispatcher** — `src/infrastructure/channels/notification-dispatcher.service.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport { TwilioSmsService } from './twilio-sms.service';\nimport { ZaloOaService } from './zalo-oa.service';\nimport { FcmPushService } from './fcm-push.service';\n\nexport type NotifyChannel = 'sms' | 'zalo' | 'fcm' | 'in_app';\n\nexport class NotificationDispatcher {\n  private sms = new TwilioSmsService();\n  private zalo = new ZaloOaService();\n  private fcm = new FcmPushService();\n\n  async dispatch(channel: NotifyChannel, payload: {\n    recipient: string; // phone for sms, zalo_user_id for zalo, fcm_token for fcm\n    title: string;\n    body: string;\n    data?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  }): Promise<{ success: boolean; channel; messageId?: string; error?: string }> {\n    try {\n      switch (channel) {\n        case 'sms': {\n          const result = await this.sms.send(payload.recipient, `${payload.title}\\n${payload.body}`);\n          return { success: true, channel, messageId: result.sid };\n        }\n        case 'zalo': {\n          const result = await this.zalo.sendText(payload.recipient, `${payload.title}\\n${payload.body}`);\n          return { success: result.success, channel, messageId: result.success ? 'ok' : undefined };\n        }\n        case 'fcm': {\n          const msgId = await this.fcm.sendToToken(payload.recipient, { title: payload.title, body: payload.body }, payload.data as Record<string, string>);\n          return { success: true, channel, messageId: msgId };\n        }\n        case 'in_app':\n        default:\n          return { success: true, channel, messageId: undefined }; // stored in DB by NotifyService\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      const error = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n      return { success: false, channel, error };\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**3. Update NotifyService.send()** — add channel dispatch after DB save:\n\nIn `notify.service.ts`, after `repo.sendNotification(data)` succeeds, call `dispatcher.dispatch()` for each channel in `data.channels || ['in_app']`. Map `sms→recipient phone`, `zalo→zalo_user_id`, `fcm→fcm_token`. These come from the user document.\n\n**4. Update .env.example** — add:\n```env\n# Twilio SMS\nTWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your_twilio_account_sid\nTWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your_twilio_auth_token\nTWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1234567890\n\n# Zalo OA\nZALO_APP_ID=your_zalo_app_id\nZALO_APP_SECRET=your_zalo_app_secret\nZALO_OA_ID=your_zalo_oa_id\n\n# Firebase Cloud Messaging\nFIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT={\"type\":\"service_account\"...}\n```\n\n### Requirements\n- Create directory `src/infrastructure/channels/` with all 4 files\n- Install missing deps: `yarn add twilio firebase-admin` and `yarn add -D @types/twilio`\n- Update `NotifyService.send()` to call the dispatcher\n- Update `.env.example` with all placeholder keys\n- Run `yarn build` after — must pass with no errors\n- DO NOT push to remote — commit local only\n\n### Deliverables\n- All 4 channel service files created\n- `notify.service.ts` updated with dispatch calls\n- `.env.example` updated\n- `yarn build` passes\n- Commit with message: `feat(notification): add Twilio SMS, Zalo OA, and FCM push channel dispatchers`\n\nStart now.","label":"ahv-qlhv-be:senior-backend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","timeoutSeconds":600,"mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":269,"output":2184,"cacheRead":56111,"cacheWrite":577,"totalTokens":59141,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776285821027,"responseId":"062f2b7e4a1005fa7afb11724e5c0758"}}
