{"type":"message","id":"1fdca6fd","parentId":"f85e1747","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:44:34.554Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Swagger is very minimal - only basic GET/POST for each route, no request/response body schemas, no parameters, etc. I need to enhance this significantly. But I should focus on completing it comprehensively.\n\nLet me now look at all the controllers to understand what routes are missing from Swagger:\n1. city.routes: 4 routes\n2. course.routes: 11 routes \n3. dashboard.routes: 1 route\n4. dat.routes: 3 routes\n5. data.routes: 2 routes (missing from swagger)\n6. exam.routes: 10 routes\n7. exam_batch.routes: 6 routes (missing POST, PUT, DELETE from swagger)\n\n\n8. exam_schedule.routes: 6 routes (missing from swagger)\n9. lesson.routes: 7 routes (missing POST, PUT, DELETE, import from swagger)\n10. license-category.routes: 4 routes (missing from swagger)\n11. license_category.routes: 5 routes (duplicate - both exist)\n12. notification.routes: 5 routes (missing most from swagger)\n13. payment.routes: 8 routes (missing PUT, DELETE)\n14. settings.routes: 2 routes\n15. stadium.routes: 5 routes (missing PUT, DELETE)\n16. student.routes: 10 routes (missing PUT, DELETE, import)\n17. vip_qr.routes: 2 routes\n18. auth.routes: 8 routes (missing PUT, DELETE)\n\nThere's a significant gap between what's actually implemented and what's documented - I'm missing many POST, PUT, and DELETE operations across almost every route, plus there are duplicate license category routes that need consolidation. I need to systematically go through each controller to understand the full API surface before I can document everything properly. the real routes from the actual controllers.\n\nLet me read the key controllers to get the accurate route list. I'll focus on building a comprehensive swagger with proper schemas.\n\nActually, let me do this efficiently. I'll read the key controllers and build the swagger.json programmatically. But first, let me check what's the state of each controller to understand which routes are critical.\n\nLet me focus on:\n1. Reading key controllers to understand their methods\n2. Building comprehensive swagger.json\n3. Writing to file\n\nLet me start by reading the controllers with the most routes to understand the patterns.","thinkingSignature":"4c40487c8c2a99546df70c582280af4cbfd52ddbc132bc440dea7de8622303bf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xnft71kkg87f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Get all route definitions from controllers\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\nfor f in src/interface/controllers/*.ts; do\n  name=$(basename \"$f\" .ts)\n  routes=$(grep -E \"^(export const|export async)\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null | sed 's/export const \\|export async function //' | cut -d' ' -f1 | tr '\\n' ', ' | sed 's/,$//')\n  echo \"=== $name ===\"\n  echo \"  Functions: $routes\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2456,"output":622,"cacheRead":56827,"cacheWrite":2498,"totalTokens":62403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776285857958,"responseId":"062f2ba37b9bd2cf06336fc08cbe3533"}}
