{"type":"message","id":"fbfdd409","parentId":"01395a75","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:51:20.474Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bwm8to2xhe40_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT\n\n## QLHV Driving — Driver Training Management System\n\n| Field              | Value                                                 |\n| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Version**        | v1.0                                                  |\n| **Created**        | April 2026                                            |\n| **Classification** | Internal Document                                     |\n| **Product**        | QLHV Driving (Web App)                                |\n| **Platform**       | Web (Mobile-first Responsive)                         |\n| **Backend**        | Node.js, Express.js + TypeScript (Clean Architecture) |\n| **Database**       | MongoDB                                               |\n| **Status**         | Draft — In Development                                |\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [Product Overview](#1-product-overview)\n2. [System Architecture](#2-system-architecture)\n3. [Feature Details](#3-feature-details)\n4. [Non-Functional Requirements](#4-non-functional-requirements)\n5. [MVP & Development Roadmap](#5-mvp--development-roadmap)\n6. [UX & Design Principles](#6-ux--design-principles)\n7. [Constraints & Risks](#7-constraints--risks)\n8. [Success Criteria & Metrics](#8-success-criteria--metrics)\n9. [Appendices](#9-appendices)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Product Overview\n\n### 1.1 Description\n\nQLHV Driving is a comprehensive web application designed for driving training centers and enrollment agencies. The system allows tracking students from registration to passing their driving test, managing tuition fees, exam schedules, and sending automated notifications.\n\n### 1.2 Product Objectives\n\n- Digitize student management workflows — completely eliminating manual paperwork.\n- Provide an intuitive dashboard for management to quickly grasp the situation.\n- Automate reminders for tuition fees and exam schedules via Zalo OA / SMS.\n- Centralize data storage in a secure MongoDB database.\n- Support multi-device access: desktop and mobile (responsive design).\n\n### 1.3 User Personas\n\n| User                          | Description                                                      |\n| ----------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Administrator**             | Center Owner / Director — Full access to configuration and data. |\n| **Admissions Officer**        | Enter new student data, collect tuition fees, update statuses.   |\n| **Instructor / Exam Officer** | Track learning progress, enter exam results.                     |\n| **Student (Indirect)**        | Receive notifications via Zalo / SMS — No direct login.          |\n\n---\n\n## 2. System Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Technology Stack\n\n| Component      | Detail                                                |\n| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Frontend**   | Next.js — Client-Side Rendering (TypeScript)          |\n| **Backend**    | Node.js, Express.js + TypeScript (Clean Architecture) |\n| **Database**   | MongoDB                                               |\n| **Charts**     | Chart.js v4.4.1                                       |\n| **Icons**      | Lucide                                                |\n| **Typography** | Be Vietnam Pro (Google Fonts)                         |\n| **Auth**       | JWT + OAuth 2.0                                       |\n| **Logging**    | Winston (Mandatory)                                   |\n\n### 2.2 Clean Architecture Structure (Backend)\n\nThe backend follows a strict 3-layer Clean Architecture pattern:\n\n| Layer              | Path                  | Responsibility                                                   |\n| ------------------ | --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Domain**         | `src/domain/`         | Enterprise business logic, entities, and repository interfaces.  |\n| **Application**    | `src/application/`    | Use cases (services), command/query handlers.                    |\n| **Infrastructure** | `src/infrastructure/` | Database repositories (MongoDB), external API adapters, loggers. |\n| **Interface**      | `src/interface/`      | Controllers, routes, and JSON envelopes.                         |\n\n#### Key Architectural Constraints:\n\n- **Path Aliases**: `@/` must be used for all imports.\n- **Strict JSON Envelope**: All endpoints must return a consistent JSON response format.\n- **Error Handling**: Use `catchAsync` in controllers; avoid manual try/catch blocks.\n- **Services**: Must use instance methods (no static methods).\n- **No Console Logs**: Use Winston logger exclusively.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Feature Details\n\n### 3.1 Dashboard — Overview\n\nHome page displaying the status of all students via data cards and intuitive charts.\n\n| Feature         | Description                                                                                                                                     | Priority |   Status    |\n| --------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :------: | :---------: |\n| Status Cards    | 9 status cards: Total Students, Pending Health Check, Health Check Done, Docs Submitted, Studying, Testing, Passed, Failed, Outstanding Balance |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Upcoming Exams  | List of exam batches in the next 7 days.                                                                                                        |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Recent Students | Table of the 5 most recently registered students.                                                                                               |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Regional Chart  | Bar chart showing students by enrollment region.                                                                                                |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Status Chart    | Donut chart showing student status distribution.                                                                                                |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 3.2 Student Management\n\nThe central module where the entire student lifecycle is managed.\n\n| Feature                | Description                                                                    | Priority |   Status    |\n| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------: | :---------: |\n| Student List           | Table (desktop) / Card list (mobile) with pagination.                          |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Pipeline Bar           | Quick filter chips for 8 statuses with counts.                                 |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Advanced Filters       | Filter by registration date, license class, region, course, search keywords.   |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Vehicle Categories     | Segment tabs: All / Motorcycles / Cars.                                        |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Student Profile        | 6-tab Detail Drawer: Profile, Health Check, Progress, Exams, Tuition, History. |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Add Student            | Quick modal with all basic information fields.                                 |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Bulk Actions           | Bulk select + bulk action (change status, delete).                             |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Export CSV             | Export the currently displayed student list to a CSV file.                     |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Print List             | Print-friendly layout for student lists.                                       |   Low    | ✅ Complete |\n| Administrative Address | Province/City → Ward/Commune selection based on Vietnam's administrative list. |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n\n#### 3.2.1 Student Status Lifecycle\n\nStudents progress through statuses in the following order:\n\n```\nPending Health Check → Health Check Done → Docs Submitted → Studying → Testing → Passed\n                                                                        ↘ Failed → (back to Testing)\n                                                                        ↘ Dropout\n```\n\n| Status           | Meaning                                 |\n| ---------------- | --------------------------------------- |\n| `pending_ksk`    | Pending health check.                   |\n| `ksk_done`       | Health check complete — eligible.       |\n| `docs_submitted` | Documents submitted to the authorities. |\n| `studying`       | Currently in the training course.       |\n| `exam`           | Assigned to an exam batch.              |\n| `passed`         | Passed exam — complete.                 |\n| `failed`         | Failed exam — waiting for re-test.      |\n| `dropout`        | Dropped out mid-course.                 |\n\n### 3.3 Course Management\n\n| Feature           | Description                                                              | Priority |   Status    |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------: | :---------: |\n| Course List       | Accordion cards displaying information + students per course.            |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Add/Edit Course   | Modal: name, start date, status, notes.                                  |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Course Stats      | 5 stat cards: Total, Draft/Upcoming, Studying, Completed, Unassigned.    |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Assign Students   | \"Unassigned\" tab — search, filter, and assign students (single or bulk). |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Delete & Reassign | Deleting a course includes an option to move students to another course. |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 3.4 Exam Schedule\n\n| Feature          | Description                                                                          | Priority |   Status    |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------: | :---------: |\n| Exam Batches     | Create batches with: name, vehicle type, region, dates, venue, status.               |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Exam Venues      | Select from a venue list (configured in Settings), showing address + Maps link.      |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Assign Students  | Modal to assign students to a batch: filter by license type, region; multi-select.   |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Enter Results    | Enter overall result (pass/fail) + failed subjects per student.                      |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Quick Entry      | Inline result entry within the batch list — no modal required.                       |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Re-test          | If failed, immediately assign to a re-test batch from the same result form.          |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Unassigned Exams | Separate tab for students not yet assigned to an exam batch (including failed ones). |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Batch Stats      | 5 cards: Total, Upcoming, Confirmed, Completed, Unassigned Students.                 |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 3.5 Tuition Fees\n\n| Feature         | Description                                                              | Priority |   Status    |\n| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------: | :---------: |\n| Debt Overview   | 4 stat cards: Total Tuition, Collected, Outstanding, Students with Debt. |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Tuition List    | Table (desktop) / Card list (mobile) + filters for region, debt status.  |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Record Payment  | Within student profile: date, amount, phase, method, receipt.            |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Payment History | Detailed table of all payments, with delete option per row.              |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Payment Bar     | Visual progress bar for paid vs. total tuition.                          |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 3.6 VIP QR Payment Integration\n\n> ⭐ **Premium Feature** — requires an activation code from the provider.\n\n| Feature           | Description                                                                    | Priority |   Status    |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------: | :---------: |\n| VNPay Integration | Integrated via VNPay Webhooks.                                                 |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Account Config    | Select Bank (BIN), account number, account name, QR template.                  |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Dynamic Content   | Templates with placeholders: `{name}`, `{phone}`, `{amount}`, `{id}`, `{uid6}` |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Quota Management  | Manage remaining QR usage, register for plan upgrades.                         |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Master Activation | Send requests and enter activation codes from the provider.                    |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 3.7 Notifications (Bot)\n\n| Feature           | Description                                                                            | Priority |   Status    |\n| ----------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :------: | :---------: |\n| Bulk Messaging    | Select audience, channel (Zalo OA / SMS), title, content.                              |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Target Groups     | Groups: All studying, Upcoming Exam (7 days), Debtors, Failed students, Region, Class. |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Dynamic Variables | Placeholders in content: `{name}`, `{class}`, `{region}`, `{exam_date}`.               |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Message Preview   | Preview messages before sending.                                                       |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| History           | Logs of sent notifications.                                                            |   Low    | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 3.8 Settings\n\n| Feature            | Description                                               | Priority |   Status    |\n| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- | :------: | :---------: |\n| Enrollment Regions | CRUD list of regions / branches.                          |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| License Classes    | CRUD license types: A1, A2, B1, B2, C...                  |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Tuition Phases     | Define collection phases (Phase 1, 2, 3...).              |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Clinics            | List of affiliated clinics / hospitals for health checks. |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Exam Venues        | CRUD exam venues: name, address, Google Maps link.        |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n| Organization Info  | Center name, address, phone number.                       |   Low    | ✅ Complete |\n| Required Fields    | Configure which fields are mandatory in student forms.    |  Medium  | ✅ Complete |\n| Data Management    | Export JSON backup, Import JSON restore, Clear all data.  |   High   | ✅ Complete |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Non-Functional Requirements\n\n### 4.1 Performance\n\n- Initial page load < 3 seconds on a 4G connection.\n- Filter / Search response < 100ms (client-side processing).\n- Render 1000+ students without lag (via pagination).\n- Asset versioning to prevent stale cache issues.\n\n### 4.2 Responsive & Mobile\n\n- Main Breakpoints: `768px` (mobile) and `900px` (tablet).\n- Mobile: Slide-over sidebar with backdrop overlay.\n- Mobile: Data tables switch to Card layouts.\n- Touch-friendly: Tap targets >= 44px.\n- Horizontal swipe for pipeline chips and filter panels.\n\n### 4.3 Security\n\n- User authentication via JWT (JSON Web Tokens).\n- MongoDB connection strings secured via environment variables.\n- Password hashing using bcrypt (no plain text storage).\n- Support for session logout and invalidation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. MVP & Development Roadmap\n\n### 5.1 MVP (Current Version — v1.0)\n\nCompleted and ready for operation:\n\n|  #  | Feature / Item                                           |  Sprint  |   Status    |\n| :-: | -------------------------------------------------------- | :------: | :---------: |\n|  1  | Overview Dashboard with status cards + charts.           | Sprint 1 | ✅ Complete |\n|  2  | Full Student CRUD (add, edit, delete, detailed profile). | Sprint 1 | ✅ Complete |\n|  3  | Status Pipeline + advanced filters + search.             | Sprint 1 | ✅ Complete |\n|  4  | Course Management (add, edit, assign students).          | Sprint 2 | ✅ Complete |\n|  5  | Exam Scheduling: batches, assigning students, results.   | Sprint 2 | ✅ Complete |\n|  6  | Tuition Management: debt tracking, payments.             | Sprint 2 | ✅ Complete |\n|  7  | Settings: regions, license types, venues.                | Sprint 3 | ✅ Complete |\n|  8  | Modern Backend: Node.js/Express + MongoDB integration.   | Sprint 3 | ✅ Complete |\n|  9  | Mobile responsive (cards, sidebar, collapsed filters).   | Sprint 3 | ✅ Complete |\n| 10  | System Auth (register, login, logout).                   | Sprint 3 | ✅ Complete |\n\n### 5.2 Roadmap — Future Versions\n\n| Version  | Timeline | Content                                                                                             |\n| -------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **v1.1** | Q3 2026  | Real Zalo OA integration (API-based messaging); SMS gateway; Advanced reporting (revenue by month). |\n| **v1.2** | Q4 2026  | Student Portal (lookup exam schedule, fees); Native mobile app (PWA); Bulk Excel import.            |\n| **v2.0** | 2027     | Multi-branch support; AI-optimized exam scheduling; Advanced analytics dashboard.                   |\n\n---\n\n## 6. UX & Design Principles\n\n### 6.1 Design System\n\n| Token             | Value                                                 |\n| ----------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Primary Color** | `#1E40AF` (Blue 800) — Main CTAs, headings.           |\n| **Accent Color**  | `#2563EB` (Blue 600) — Links, active icons.           |\n| **Success**       | `#059669` (Emerald 600) — Passed, paid status.        |\n| **Warning**       | `#D97706` (Amber 600) — Warnings, upcoming deadlines. |\n| **Danger**        | `#DC2626` (Red 600) — Errors, failed, debt.           |\n| **Typography**    | Be Vietnam Pro — Weights 300-800.                     |\n| **Border Radius** | `8px` (base), `12px` (card), `99px` (chip/badge).     |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Constraints & Risks\n\n### 7.1 Technical Constraints\n\n- MongoDB Atlas free tier limitations (storage and connections).\n- Chart.js client-side rendering — performance depends on user device.\n\n### 7.2 Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk                  | Mitigation Strategy                                             |\n| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Data Loss             | Automated MongoDB backups; JSON export feature for users.       |\n| Security Breach       | Regular dependency audits; JWT expiration; secure HTTP headers. |\n| Scalability Issues    | Horizontal scaling via Docker; database indexing optimization.  |\n| Browser Compatibility | Polyfills and testing across modern browsers (Chrome, Safari).  |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Success Criteria & Metrics\n\n### 8.1 Operational KPIs\n\n- Time to enter a new student < 2 minutes.\n- Student search response < 5 seconds.\n- 100% of exam batches recorded in the system.\n- UI error/crash rate = 0 in 30 days of operation.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Appendices\n\n### A. Project Structure (Clean Architecture)\n\n```\n/\n├── frontend/           # Next.js Application\n│   ├── public/\n│   ├── src/\n│   │   ├── components/\n│   │   ├── hooks/\n│   │   ├── services/\n│   │   └── pages/\n├── backend/            # Node.js + Express + TypeScript\n│   ├── src/\n│   │   ├── domain/         # Business logic & Entities\n│   │   ├── application/    # Use cases & Services\n│   │   ├── infrastructure/ # MongoDB Repositories & Adapters\n│   │   ├── interface/      # Controllers & Routes\n│   │   └── index.ts        # Entry point\n└── README.md\n```\n\n### B. Glossary\n\n| Term             | Explanation                                               |\n| ---------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **KSK**          | Health Check — mandatory for license application.         |\n| **Clean Arch**   | A software design pattern that separates concerns.        |\n| **VietQR**       | Vietnam's standard for bank transfer QR codes.            |\n| **Pipeline**     | The flow of student status from Pending to Passed.        |\n| **Drawer**       | Side panel for detailed student profiles.                 |\n| **Batch (Exam)** | A group of students taking an exam on the same day/venue. |\n| **Winston**      | A universal logging library for Node.js.                  |\n\n---\n\n_Internal Document — Not for external distribution_\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776286280452}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7bc6e62","parentId":"fbfdd409","timestamp":"2026-04-15T20:51:36.497Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the PRD. According to the PRD:\n\n### MVP Features (all marked ✅ Complete):\n1. Dashboard with status cards + charts\n2. Student CRUD\n3. Status Pipeline + filters\n4. Course Management\n5. Exam Scheduling\n6. Tuition Management\n7. Settings (regions, license types, venues)\n8. Backend Node.js/Express + MongoDB\n9. Mobile responsive\n10. System Auth\n\n### Roadmap v1.1 (Q3 2026):\n- Real Zalo OA integration ✅ (just implemented)\n\n\n- SMS gateway ✅ (just implemented)\n- Advanced reporting\n\n### Roadmap v1.2 (Q4 2026):\n- Student Portal\n- Native mobile app (PWA)\n- Bulk Excel import ✅ (BE has it)\n\n### v2.0 (2027):\n- Multi-branch support\n- AI-optimized exam scheduling\n- Advanced analytics\n\nSo the MVP is actually complete—all the core features are done, and I've just finished the Zalo OA and SMS gateway implementations. Now I need to look at what's blocking v1.1.\n\nLooking at the PRD checklist, everything marked as complete is done. The v1.1 roadmap items—Zalo OA and SMS—are already done, but I still need to implement the advanced reporting module. The roadmap for v1.2 mentions Student Portal, PWA mobile app, and bulk Excel import, which is partially complete on the backend. For v2.0, multi-branch support, AI exam scheduling, and advanced analytics are still ahead. Let me verify the remaining gaps in the notification system and then check the current status of the PRDs.\n\nLooking at what's actually needed for v1.1: the notification channels are done, but I should scan for any leftover TODOs or unimplemented features across the codebase, clean up code quality issues, and make sure the backend is optimized. I need to commit my work on the notification service, then move on to identifying any remaining work from the PRD.","thinkingSignature":"53819784af8e9cce0753101df